# Literature Review: Real-time analytics, incident response process agility, and enterprise cybersecurity

performance

## Introduction

The field of cybersecurity has become increasingly important in recent years due to the rising number and
sophistication of cyber threats. In order to effectively protect their systems and data, organizations need to
have robust incident response processes in place. Additionally, the ability to perform real-time analytics
plays a crucial role in enhancing incident response process agility and overall enterprise cybersecurity
performance. This literature review aims to explore the relationship between real-time analytics, incident
response process agility, and enterprise cybersecurity performance.

## Real-time Analytics

Real-time analytics refers to the process of analyzing data as soon as it is generated or received, without
any significant delay. This approach is crucial in the realm of cybersecurity, as it allows organizations to
detect and respond to security incidents in a timely manner. The ability to perform real-time analytics has
been identified as a significant trend in the business intelligence (BI) industry, with the goal of enabling
non-professional users to solve analytical tasks with little or no help from IT (Savinov, 2014).

## Incident Response Process Agility

Incident response process agility refers to the ability of an organization to quickly and effectively respond
to security incidents. Traditional systems that rely on separate technology stacks for transactional and
analytical workloads often fail to provide the necessary response time and agility required in the face
of rapidly evolving cyber threats (Bowman & Tschan, 2013). Therefore, adopting a real-time analytics
approach can significantly enhance incident response process agility.

## Enterprise Cybersecurity Performance

Enterprise cybersecurity performance refers to the overall effectiveness of an organization's cybersecurity
measures in protecting its systems and data. By leveraging real-time analytics and enhancing incident
response process agility, organizations can improve their cybersecurity performance. Real-time analytics
provides organizations with the ability to detect and respond to security incidents in real-time, minimizing
the potential impact of cyber threats. Additionally, incident response process agility allows organizations
to quickly adapt and respond to new and emerging threats, further strengthening their cybersecurity
performance.
